Briar is my 11 year old son who has worked extremely hard this past year putting up Spartan Trail Cameras, helping with food plots and hanging tree stands. I have always wanted him to earn his hunts and especially the opportunities at a big buck. This year was his year. Because he worked so hard in the off season he earned his chance at a really good deer. Early November rolled around and he finally got his chance. programme.title: Iowa

Even though we saw the shooter we were after and another really good deer, after 4 days of hunting we decided to pack up again and try our luck in Iowa. For a hard core whitetail bow hunter chasing big deer its hard to beat sitting in a tree in Iowa at the end of October and early November. We couldn't have timed this up more perfect. The bucks were on their feet, we were seeing giant deer, and it was just a matter of time before we ran in to one in bow range. Sit back and enjoy the second episode of Whitetail Edge Season 4, "Iowa".
